Text.Value: The master said you might offer to come willing, but his orders were very specific.
The scars he carved into our backs bind us to the ritual. Seven spawn, seven sigils.
Attack.
And if I refuse to come?
But if brother's right, we're more useful to him dead.
And he needs you, Astarion. It's time to come home.
He's going to end us?
Still picking fights you can't win? You always were pig-headed, brother.
*Should you face Cazador? Should you run? And what of his ritual - this 'Ascension' - how can you turn that to your advantage?*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion gets to his feet quickly, expecting a fight

Text.Value: *You're weighing up your prospects when a faint noise jerks you alert. There's someone in the dark...*
Together? Since when do you care 'bout anyone but yourself?
Maybe you could take Cazador's place. Maybe you could free us.
Of course not, the master needs us. We're loyal. And more to the point, we're useful.
Fight him? You know we can't.
You're not listening, brother. You have to come with us.
You want us to throw away our chance at freedom? On your word that you can defeat the master? Be serious.
Of course not, the master's no fool. He needs us.
Sorry, brother. This is the best we can do.
The master said bring you home - so you're coming home.
You may be free of his rules, but we're not.
*Rest does not come easy tonight. Your mind considers one future after another, teasing apart the possibilities.*
Easy to say, but we can't disobey the master. We're not as lucky as you, Astarion.
Listen to me, this ritual of Cazador's - we're part of it. He's going to sacrifice us all!
It's a lie - Cazador would never share power with us.
Not with you, maybe. Not with the runt of the kennel.

EditorData.stateContext: Astarion sitting on his bedroll in resting position

Text.Value: I can beat Cazador. Follow me, help me complete the ritual, and I'll set you free.
I'm not going anywhere with you.
All right, let's go home.
Refuse? But 'thou shalt obey me in all things'.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quoting one of his master Cazador's rules

Text.Value: The master's holding a Black Mass. That's where he'll ascend, and we'll get to live again.
You don't know? The Rite of Profane Ascension.
We've listened to you for long enough, brother. We have our commands.
And you're number seven - the final piece of the Rite. He needs us all for the Black Mass.
What ritual? What are you talking about?
Follow you? The runt of the kennel? Master's favourite toy?
Maybe. Don't change nothing, though.
When the master ascends, he'll take us with him. We'll all be free.
The master told us to take you alive. 'As broken as possible, but alive.'
You were always weak, brother. We don't follow weak.
Master said bring him home. Master said to fight... Never forbade us from talking, though.
We'll walk in the sun. We won't feel hungry all the time. We'll be living vampires.
It seems Petras was right - the rules no longer apply to our dear brother.
You do look different - stronger, fire in your eyes.
Peace, brother. We're just here to take you home.
Don't matter. The master needs all seven of us for the ritual.
Shit.

EditorData.NodeContext: He was creeping up on a resting Astarion, but Astarion woke up and spotted him.
EditorData.SFXTags: [DP] Faint noise in Distance, could be a footstep, or a bump or something, as long as it works in both Elfsong and Slums Camps

Text.Value: What if we joined together? Fought Cazador together?
Then we'll die! Unlike our sweet brother, we've no choice but to obey.
Looks like the rules no longer apply to our dear brother. Curious.
We'll walk in the sun. We'll finally be free, brother.

Synopsis: Astarion-avatar gets attacked by a group of vampire spawns during a long rest
